The following issues were recently filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission: 

American Capital & Research Corp., initial offering of 3,874,000 class A common shares, of which 3.5 million will be offered by the company, and the balance by holders, via Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc., Alex.
Brown & Sons Inc., and Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. 

Nuveen New York Performance Plus Municipal Fund Inc., initial offering of five million common shares, via Alex.
Brown, John Nuveen & Co., and Prudential-Bache Capital Funding. 

Turkish Investment Fund Inc., initial offering of five million common shares, via International Finance Corp., Salomon Brothers Inc., Merrill Lynch Capital Markets, Deutsche Bank Capital Corp., Morgan Stanley & Co., and Nomura Securities International Inc. 

Wolverine Exploration Co., offering of 1.2 million common shares, via Smith Barney, Harris Upham & Co. and Alex.
Brown. 

